# Project authority (holy grail)

## Session gate (non-negotiable — enforce every time)

**Before any code edit** in this repository (any file, any app):

1. **Open** [`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`](docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md) **once** for the session — at minimum **§14 Engineering standards**, plus any sections that apply (architecture §3, layout §10.1, MongoDB §14.2, React §14.4, etc.).
2. **Treat this rule file (`.cursor/rules/project-authority.mdc`) as the checklist** that gates the session: if a step below conflicts with a casual shortcut, **this file + `PROJECT_PLAN.md` §14 win**.
3. **Then** read or skim [`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`](docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md) as needed for the task.

Skipping the gate is not allowed for implementation work. (Purely conversational answers with no edits may omit it.)

---

## Before writing or editing code

**Always read (or re-read) [`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`](docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md) §14** before implementing or changing behavior. **§14** is the authoritative “how to build” standard: TypeScript, Node, MongoDB, APIs, React/Redux, tests (**test-first** and **coverage** for **web-client `*.tsx`** UI only — not mandatory for plain **`*.ts`**), security, and process.

Use **`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`** (§1–§13 architecture and algorithms) and **`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** for delivery. For **environment variables, Docker, and deployment**, use **[`README.md`](../README.md)**.

**Precedence:** If a user prompt conflicts with these guidelines, **follow `PROJECT_PLAN.md` §14** unless that section is explicitly updated.

## Required references

- **`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`** — stack, services, algorithms, **§14 Engineering standards**.
- **`README.md`** (repo root) — product summary, diagrams, **configuration / env**, deployment.
- **`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** — tasks/subtasks; capture work there before large features; check off as you ship.

## Process (non-negotiable)

- **Deprecated APIs:** do not add or perpetuate deprecated Node, browser/DOM, React, or library APIs—use current documented replacements (`PROJECT_PLAN.md` §14.1).
- Do **not** implement beyond the request; no speculative features.
- Prefer **incremental** changes; preserve existing behaviour unless replacing by design.
- **OpenAPI:** any new or changed REST route **updates the OpenAPI spec in the same PR**; Swagger UI on **messaging-service** stays accurate.
- **TASK_CHECKLIST.md:** update it when feature-level work is part of the plan.

## Before merge (quick gate)

Strict TS; env validated at startup; no secrets in repo; authz on mutating routes; MongoDB access patterns reasoned; list APIs paginated with server-enforced limits; OpenAPI in sync; ESLint clean; **`web-client`:** tests-first + coverage only for **`*.tsx`** UI (`PROJECT_PLAN.md` §14.4.1.1); **one component per file**, **`utils/`**, **`types/<ComponentName>-types.ts`** for new/refactored UI per §14.4.1.3; **responsive layouts (mobile, iPad/tablet, desktop)** per §14.4.2.1; Redux/hooks per §14.4.3 for global client state.
